WEBVTT

00:01.617 --> 00:06.823
economic forces play a great role in shaping any 
community. How would you say that economic

00:06.843 --> 00:11.989
influence has been an impact in planning in 
Austin? Austin's been very fortunate, as I think

00:13.871 --> 00:17.996
you'll find most centers of government. With the 
high percentage of government employment,

00:23.065 --> 00:25.650
Austin's been immune from the business cycle. 
Recessions don't tend to hit Austin.

00:28.715 --> 00:30.639
Unemployment doesn't tend to hit Austin. We've 
always had one of the lowest unemployment in the

00:30.659 --> 00:35.007
entire state, if not the nation. For a city in the 
size category. Well, for any city, really. For any

00:40.637 --> 00:41.319
city. I think it's characteristic of most centers 
of government.

00:48.378 --> 00:50.902
So Austin has not been diversified. It's been made 
up of three sectors, government, military, which

00:50.982 --> 01:01.720
is not a tremendous amount, but it's significant, 
and the city of Austin. The city of Austin is one of

01:01.860 --> 01:06.568
the largest employers in the entire area. 
Primarily because they own the utility system,

01:06.588 --> 01:12.698
there's over 8,000 employees in the city of 
Austin. It's been in the past five years, or maybe

01:13.471 --> 01:26.148
since the beginning of the Austin Memorial 
Program in the early 70s, that the Chamber of

01:13.471 --> 01:26.148
Commerce began a very strong and well-financed 
operation to diversify Austin's economy. That

01:26.749 --> 01:38.685
has resulted over the past three years with a very 
noticeable and predictable shift of electronics

01:26.749 --> 01:38.685
manufacturing from Silicon Valley in California 
near San Francisco. Firms are coming to Austin to

01:45.085 --> 01:47.729
establish new plants. There's very good reasons 
why they're doing that. They find that in

01:50.974 --> 01:54.719
California they're robbing from each other now 
for the talent pool. And here's Austin with a huge

01:55.981 --> 02:01.929
university, a tremendously good environment, 
and a new opportunity. Well IBM came, Texas

02:02.169 --> 02:06.816
Instruments came, Now we find Data General 
Corporation coming. We find three or four other

02:10.442 --> 02:17.672
computer firms moving in from Silicon Valley and 
other parts of the country. And we see Austin's

02:18.312 --> 02:25.082
electronic manufacturing employment 
skyrocketing. As an example, five years ago,

02:26.764 --> 02:36.077
there might have been two lines of advertising for 
electrical engineering people semiconductor

02:36.428 --> 02:37.670
people. Now there's two pages of them. And 
Austin's headed down the same road as Silicon

02:40.234 --> 02:42.678
Valley. There will be a saturation, in my view, in 
the next ten years of electronics firms. As a

02:48.888 --> 02:53.436
result, Austin is liable to face the same kind of 
activity that Silicon Valley had. A tremendous

02:53.456 --> 03:00.968
competition for labor, increased labor costs, 
and of course with that will come greater

02:53.456 --> 03:00.968
in-migration more white collar and higher 
educated people and you will see Austin continue

03:01.960 --> 03:08.991
to attract the white collar, high income pool of 
people. Where has that type of so-called clean

03:09.973 --> 03:13.759
industry been sown in Austin? Anywhere they want. 
Anywhere they want. Undeveloped land usually or

03:18.867 --> 03:22.854
has land been cleared, let's say slum clearance? 
No, there's been no clearance. There has been no

03:25.278 --> 03:28.643
centralization either. IBM is just going through 
a doubling in the size of its plant. Texas

03:34.224 --> 03:40.374
Instruments, about 8, 9, 10 miles away, outside 
the city limits, was only annexed a few years ago.

03:40.974 --> 03:44.940
There's two large firms in the south just coming 
in. There's one in the west. Motorola has its

03:46.202 --> 03:48.546
second plant location. It has a large 
semiconductor facility on the east side. Tracor

03:51.730 --> 03:58.360
Corporation, which is a large electronics 
manufacturer, is on the east side. And so they're

03:59.015 --> 04:00.617
just ringing the city. There has not been a 
dedicated interest because of the price of cheap

04:01.398 --> 04:04.863
land. And the availability of land, there's not 
been any interest in coming in and going to the

04:05.744 --> 04:12.794
expense of clearing and going into an inner city. 
Mobility is easy in Austin. It doesn't take very

04:17.220 --> 04:20.164
long to get north, south, east, or west. And so they 
choose the cheapest alternative that they can. Do

04:25.791 --> 04:27.874
planners receive a great deal of problems, 
