04:46.144 --> 04:51.870
ago began the development of ring freeways. and 
though citizens have expressed opposition to

04:52.981 --> 05:08.177
that, we find that a significant highway's been 
built right through the hill country,

04:52.981 --> 05:08.177
significant bridge is going to be built right over 
the lake that was not really beneficial. No one

05:08.217 --> 05:10.660
wanted it to happen, but the state did it anyway.

05:13.323 --> 05:14.604
Tremendous conflicts there. I see Austin 
continuing down the road of an inner loop, and then

05:15.045 --> 05:21.992
an outer loop, virtually the same shape that 
American cities have taken all over the country.

05:26.349 --> 05:28.833
We've almost completed the inner loop. We've 
already seen plans for an outer loop. And though

05:32.419 --> 05:39.690
there's none under construction, we now have 
freeway presentations and freeway proposals

05:32.419 --> 05:39.690
being looked at for other arteries of this 
community. And I think that runs counter to the

05:40.832 --> 05:44.297
master plan. But yet, everything continues in 
spite of that. It also seems to run counter to the

05:47.822 --> 05:50.106
master plan that growth is to be managed, but at the 
